This paper deals with the analysis of wireless communication networks, specifically Cell-Free Massive MIMO networks. The paper discusses the impact of stochastic geometry on channel hardening and favorable propagation in these networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their information-carrying capacity. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), as the paper also discusses resource allocation schemes and optimization techniques for these networks.
